./CHANGELOG.md:350:- Added depth-2 sample-record audio-analysis end-to-end test coverage (frac-0109): `tests/test_sample_record_audio_analysis.py` now includes `SampleRecordAudioAnalysisEndToEndTests`, which drives `SampleRecord` audio metrics through one real WAV-backed lifecycle: construction with meaningful `duration`/`rms`/`peak`/`transient_density`, `to_dict()` JSON compatibility, `SampleRecord.from_dict(...)` restoration, `SampleLibrary.add(...)` SQLite persistence, filtered `SampleLibrary.find(...)` retrieval by source/tag/mood, and JSON-safe diagnostic round-tripping. `tests/test_test_sample_record_audio_analysis_depth.py` pins the test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the named end-to-end class/method. Existing production behavior remains unchanged because `senseweave.sample_library` already persisted full record JSON; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4655 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
./CHANGELOG.md:358:- Added depth-2 render-replay end-to-end test coverage (frac-0105): `tests/test_render_replay.py` now includes `RenderReplayEndToEndTests`, which drives the existing `my-claw/tools/senseweave/render/replay.py` public surface through one mapping-score → sidecar-delta → performed-part → audio-export → persisted-delta replay lifecycle. The coverage verifies score-event dictionaries are coerced into rendered `Event` objects, score-level fields remain owned by the original score even when deltas repeat `pitch`/`role`/`nominal_beat`, performance fields and sensor deltas are overlaid, `seed_path` values replay as tuples, duplicate rule-stack entries collapse into ordered unique `applied_rules`, seed metadata is preserved as strings, diagnostics round-trip through `json.dumps(..., sort_keys=True)`, `export_audio(...)` persists the default `.delta.json` track and readable sidecar, and replaying from the persisted delta path reproduces the original event-sequence hash. `tests/test_test_render_replay_depth.py` pins the render-replay test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the named end-to-end class/method. Existing production behavior remains unchanged because the replay module already produced meaningful one-path output; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4635 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
./CHANGELOG.md:392:- Added depth-2 musical-integration-runtime end-to-end test coverage (frac-0092): `tests/test_musical_integration_runtime.py` now includes `MusicalIntegrationRuntimeEndToEndTests`, which drives the existing musical runtime public surface through one room-mic scene: `senseweave.sample_dsp_activity.build_sample_dsp_activity(...)`, `sample_playback_engine.maybe_launch_event(...)` (with `STATE_PATH`, `OUTPUT_DIR`, and `launch_pw_play` patched for hermetic execution), the on-disk playback state, `self_listener.build_glyph_audio_state(...)`, `senseweave.sample_status.sample_status_text(...)`, and a JSON-safe combined `{activity, playback_state, glyph, face_text}` diagnostic round trip. `tests/test_test_musical_integration_runtime_depth.py` pins the test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. Existing production `sample_playback_engine`, `self_listener`, and senseweave sample helpers remain unchanged because they already produced meaningful one-path output; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4578 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
./CHANGELOG.md:448:- Added depth-2 local-client end-to-end test coverage (frac-0064): `tests/test_client_local.py` now includes `TestLocalAdaClientEndToEnd`, which drives the existing `LocalAdaClient` public surface through typed `GenerationRequest` and legacy mapping paths. The new tests verify typed requests produce real mono WAV previews with stable local request ids, protocol summaries, zero-cost metadata, expected latency from an injected clock, valid WAV container metadata, nonzero frames, and passing `validate_generation_result` outcomes; verify mapping requests return queue/cache/storage-ready payloads with `prediction_id`, `api_request_id`, `request_id`, `audio_path`, `sample_rate`, duration, model, cost, per-second cost, and nonnegative latency; round-trip request summaries and combined diagnostics through `json.dumps`; and confirm repeated mapping generation reuses the same deterministic path and bytes. `tests/test_test_client_local_depth.py` pins `tests/test_client_local.py` at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. Existing local-client assertions and production `my-claw/tools/senseweave/generation/client_local.py` behavior remain unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4414 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green.
./CHANGELOG.md:456:- Added depth-2 audio-analysis end-to-end test coverage (frac-0060): `tests/test_audio_analysis.py` now includes `TestAudioAnalysisEndToEnd`, which drives the existing pure `audio_analysis` public API through complete synthetic listening paths. The new tests analyze tonal sine signals through amplitude, autocorrelation pitch, note/key mapping, content classification, and spectral peak extraction; classify deterministic speech-like dynamic material; retain a sparse impulse through click-transient detection and transient classification; derive silence/onset/sustain/release transitions from windowed RMS values; and confirm public outputs can be serialized into JSON-safe diagnostics. `tests/test_audio_analysis_depth.py` pins the file's fractal depth at >= 2 (now `substantial (no tests)`, 21 trivial functions versus 24 real). Existing audio-analysis assertions and `my-claw/tools/audio_analysis.py` behavior remain unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate remain green.
./CHANGELOG.md:552:- Added depth-2 local generation backend behavior (frac-0011): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/generation/client_local.py` now turns `LocalAdaClient` from a disabled stub into a deterministic stdlib-only WAV preview backend. Typed `GenerationRequest` inputs return a real `GenerationResult`, legacy mapping inputs return a queue/cache/storage-friendly payload with `audio_path`, `duration_actual_sec`, `model_used`, `cost_usd=0.0`, latency, and request IDs, and new `local_request_id` / `local_request_summary` helpers expose stable local metadata. `tests/test_client_local_depth.py` pins meaningful summaries, typed WAV output, mapping end-to-end payload shape, deterministic repeat generation, and fractal depth >= 2; existing protocol, Replicate, Modal, local-client, and startup identity anchor tests remain regression coverage.
./CHANGELOG.md:590:- Added an operator runbook for the generation backend (T-011): new `docs/runbooks/generation-backend.md` documents how to check generation status, widen/tighten the daily and monthly USD budget caps (`CYPHERCLAW_GENERATION_DAILY_CAP_USD` default `5.0`, `CYPHERCLAW_GENERATION_MONTHLY_CAP_USD` default `100.0`), switch between Replicate / Modal / local backends, roll back the IDyOM long-term model from the immutable week-0 snapshot when the weekly collapse audit fires, clear stuck `running` rows from `/home/user/cypherclaw-data/generation_queue.db`, inspect the LRU cache at `/home/user/cypherclaw-data/cache/`, and find generated audio (`samples/generated/<YYYY-MM-DD>/<request_hash>.wav`) and journals (`/home/user/cypherclaw-data/state/sensory_journal.jsonl`, `samples/usage_journal.jsonl`). The runbook documents every env var the generation system reads (`CYPHERCLAW_GENERATION_DAILY_CAP_USD`, `CYPHERCLAW_GENERATION_MONTHLY_CAP_USD`, `IDYOM_KL_AUDIT_CONFIG`, `REPLICATE_API_TOKEN`, `MODAL_TOKEN_ID`, `MODAL_TOKEN_SECRET`) with defaults, calls out that all rollovers are UTC, links the canonical `sdp/telemetry/cost-model.md` and `idyom_kl_audit_config.json.example`, and includes five worked debugging scenarios (cap breach, wedged `running` row, cold cache, collapse alert rollback, Replicate→Modal failover). Locked against drift by `tests/test_runbook_generation_backend.py`, which pins the runbook's title style, required workflow coverage, env-var documentation, exactly-five `### Scenario N` headings, and on-disk path / cross-link integrity.
./CHANGELOG.md:600:- Wired `GenerationQueue` into the generation pipeline: updated its constructor to accept pipeline dependencies (`client`, `cache`, `budget`, `storage`) and implemented a `process_one()` method acting as a single-iteration worker loop that dequeues an item, generates audio, stores it, and marks the job done or failed. Added an integration test to verify the end-to-end processing pipeline on a mock client and storage.
./CHANGELOG.md:622:- Added `docs/cypherclaw-sampler-architecture.md` to fill the gap between the sampler PRD and the musicianship roadmap: it lists the landed sampler components (`sample_capture_daemon.py`, `sample_capture_verify.py`, `sampler_buffers.py`, `sampler_dispatch.py`, `synthesis/sampler_effects.scd`, `render/antipatterns.py`), traces the end-to-end signal flow from JACK input through capture, tagging, `index.sqlite`, dispatch, the `sw_sampler_fx` bus, and the master bus, names both live anti-pattern detectors (`sampler_dominating`, `sampler_silent_quintet_member`), enumerates integration seams (identity, cast planner, mix engine, composer, operator diagnostics), and explicitly flags `SampleLibrary`, `SampleSelector`, `sw_sampler.scd`, and quintet identity convergence as still pending; `tests/test_cypherclaw_sampler_architecture.py` pins the doc's required sections, the referenced file paths, and the live anti-pattern names so future renames or section drops force the doc to update with the code.
./CHANGELOG.md:625:- Closed the server-side gap on the new master-bus sampler controls: added a `master_smooth.scd` SuperCollider source stub for `sw_master_smooth` that declares `sampler_amp` and `sampler_bypass_comp` (both default 1.0) alongside the existing `amp` / `drive` / `warmth` / `reverb` / `room` surface; refactored `start_audio.sh` and `restart_composer.sh` to seed the master node via `senseweave.master_bus.master_bus_s_new_args()` so the boot-time `/s_new sw_master_smooth` arg list stays in lockstep with `DEFAULT_MASTER_BUS_VALUES`; added `tests/test_master_smooth_scd.py` to pin the stub's control declarations and the boot scripts' helper-driven seeding.
./CHANGELOG.md:628:- Added audio-rendered novelty verification for SenseWeave fixtures: `render.audio_novelty` now writes deterministic 5-minute proxy WAVs, extracts librosa mel-feature self-similarity matrices plus Foote novelty curves, aligns symbolic CCH-034 novelty peak times to audio peaks within 500 ms, and fails flattened synthesis even when symbolic metrics remain healthy.
./CHANGELOG.md:634:- Added SuperCollider recipe references for curriculum: created 22 discoverable recipe files in `my-claw/curriculum/recipes/supercollider/` for topics from MIDI-to-frequency to master-bus, linked them from EMSD-102 and EMSD-130 reference docs, and added static validation tests in `tests/test_supercollider_recipes.py` that check for required labels without coupling to the live audio server.
./CHANGELOG.md:636:- Added post-tonal, spectral, and microtonal material strategies: extended `music_theory.py` with `PitchClassSet`, `spectral_partials`, `quarter_tone_to_freq`, and `just_intonation_chord`; added `extract_spectral_peaks` to `audio_analysis.py` for SenseWeave seeding; and wired `harmonic_planner.py` to return avant-garde strategies when requested by phase/style.
./CHANGELOG.md:640:- Added live-buffer and sample-bank abstractions for SenseWeave inputs: new `live_buffer.py` module provides `LiveBuffer` for stable real-time environmental audio state (source name, capture path, freshness, RMS, spectral profile, transform history) and `SampleBankArchive` for retaining selected clips to archive storage with JSON metadata sidecars.
./CHANGELOG.md:656:- Fixed a live capture fallback issue that made the sampler lean on a quiet self bus: `room_listener.py` now skips absent named JACK ports and tries direct `jack_rec` fallback ports such as `system:capture_1`, while `sample_dsp_activity.py` now resolves missing `theramini_in` to `contact_mic` / `room_mic` before `self_bus`.
./CHANGELOG.md:664:- Hardened the local webcam path: `observer_vision.py` now defaults to `/dev/video0`, records `video_device`, and rejects stale old JPEGs when `ffmpeg` capture fails; `room_presence_daemon.py` can now run in `--observer-frame-only` mode and report `capture_source: "observer_frame"` so presence can share the single observer webcam instead of contending for it.
./CHANGELOG.md:668:- Made the self-monitor more truthful: `self_listener.py` now derives glyph-facing brightness and motion from captured audio features instead of target-only metadata, while `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh` pins the live meter to the verified JACK path on CypherClaw and still leaves PipeWire / `pw-jack` capture as fallback code paths.
./CHANGELOG.md:669:- Fixed the remaining live self-monitor blackout path: when direct `jack_rec` capture times out, `self_listener.py` now falls back to analyzing a fresh `/tmp/room_capture.wav` clip instead of writing a dark `capture_timeout` state, so glyph and sampler decisions stay audio-derived on boxes where the JACK recorder hangs.
./CHANGELOG.md:672:- Collapsed split boot ownership for the core AV stack: `cypherclaw_boot.sh` now delegates audio/composer/face/gallery/room-listener/sample startup to `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh`, which keeps one authority for those daemons instead of racing duplicate boot paths.
./CHANGELOG.md:674:- Hardened the live audio runtime after the Scarlett/JACK outage: `start_audio.sh` now links the repo SynthDef bundle into `~/.local/share/SuperCollider/synthdefs`, starts `scsynth` with synthdef auto-load enabled, and prefers a real JACK/Scarlett graph before falling back to `pw-jack`; `restart_composer.sh` now restarts the composer gracefully and verifies the new PID instead of rebuilding synthdefs with `/d_recv`; and `cypherclaw_boot.sh` no longer blindly sends `/n_set` to master node `99999` after boot.
./CHANGELOG.md:675:- Tightened that audio-runtime recovery again so `start_audio.sh` only stays on the real-JACK path when `system:playback_1` is actually present, and it now retries `scsynth` on `pw-jack` automatically if the real JACK graph disappears or never registers `SuperCollider:out_1`.
./CHANGELOG.md:676:- Made the Scarlett recovery path deterministic: when real JACK needs to be rebuilt, `start_audio.sh` now clears stale JACK state, relaunches `jackdbus`, and configures the ALSA backend for `hw:USB` before starting `scsynth`, so the box can recover onto the Scarlett monitor path instead of drifting into a PipeWire-only fallback.
./CHANGELOG.md:679:- Added a persistent cold-boot path for the live AV runtime: `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh` now restarts `start_audio.sh`, `restart_composer.sh`, `self_listener.py`, `room_listener.py`, `sample_playback_engine.py`, and `face_display.py` under detached sessions, and `cypherclaw-av-stack.service` can bind that stack to `graphical.target` so music and the face monitor return after reboot without a manual SSH recovery.
./CHANGELOG.md:681:- Made the cold-boot wrapper opportunistic instead of combative: if `scsynth` and `duet_composer.py` are already present from another startup path, `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh` now skips `start_audio.sh` / `restart_composer.sh` entirely and only backfills the missing meter/listener surface.
./CHANGELOG.md:682:- Made `self_listener.py` backend-aware: it now auto-selects between `jack_rec` and `pw-jack jack_rec`, sets `JACK_NO_START_SERVER=1` on its capture probes to avoid waking an unwanted JACK server, and publishes `capture_backend` in `/tmp/self_listen.json` so operators can tell which live graph the meter is following.
./CHANGELOG.md:684:- Made the cold-boot meter less ambiguous: `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh` now chooses `SELF_LISTENER_CAPTURE_BACKEND` from the boot-time graph decision, preferring a live PipeWire sink monitor before JACK fallbacks, and it performs a second delayed dedupe pass so late-start room/sampler/face daemons from other boot hooks are collapsed back to one process each.
./CHANGELOG.md:685:- Swapped the self-listener toward a host-stable monitor path: `self_listener.py` now prefers a PipeWire sink monitor target when one is available, still falls back to direct JACK or `pw-jack` port capture when needed, and keeps the old backend cache/reprobe logic only as fallback behavior instead of the primary live path.
./CHANGELOG.md:693:- Fixed room-capture triggering so external sample sources no longer depend on `self_listener` RMS. `room_mic`, `contact_mic`, and `theramini_in` now trigger from their own live cues, while only `self_bus` remains gated by self-audio level.
./CHANGELOG.md:696:- Promoted the Perform-VE room mic to the actual live capture path: `cypherclaw_boot.sh` now starts `room_listener.py` without `--no-jack`, and `room_listener.py` now reports `capture_backend` / `capture_source` so the live state shows whether JACK on the condenser path or an ALSA fallback is in use.
./CHANGELOG.md:697:- Adjusted room-listener fallback priority so ALSA auto-selection now prefers the Perform-VE interface over webcam or generic analog capture when JACK is unavailable.
./CHANGELOG.md:699:- Made Perform-VE usable through the Linux audio stack by teaching `room_listener.py` to prefer a PipeWire `pw-record` target for Perform-VE before trying JACK or ALSA fallbacks.
./CHANGELOG.md:705:- Wired the next EMSD runtime pass into live state: added `emsd_runtime.py`, taught `duet_composer.py` to build a typed EMSD context per tracker song and publish arc/mix/sample/DSP/identity fields into `/tmp/composer_state.json`, extended `repertoire_memory.py` to retain `patch_name`, and taught `self_listener.py` to publish `/tmp/glyph_audio_features.json` by combining live audio analysis with composer/cadence state for GlyphWeave-facing consumers.
./CHANGELOG.md:742:- Added a concrete CypherClaw upgrade checklist covering phase status, owned files, test gates, and live deployment order for the presence/cadence/personality/audio-efficiency program.
