y-claw/tools/sample_capture_daemon.py\\`.\n\n## Issues Found\n- [x] (Minor) \\`pytest tests/ -x\\` fails on macOS due to Seatbelt restrictions (\\`PermissionError\\` on \\`~/.promptclaw/pets.json\\`), but the task-specific smoke tests pass locally and the CI job runs on Linux. This is a pre-existing environment issue and does not block the specific task.\n\n## Verdict: PASS\n\n## Notes for Lead Agent\nThe wiring of \\`bootstrap_identity()\\` in \\`sample_capture_daemon.py\\` main entry point correctly addresses the hardening concern for first-boot identity minting. The CI job is well-scoped to ensure fast feedback on detector logic regressions.\nEOF\n"}}
