| CCS-023 | Per-mode sampler density gates: composer plays `floor(sampler_density * total_phrases) + Bernoulli(sampler_density)` sampler events per piece (clamped 0..total). | MUST | T1 | - `tools/duet_composer.py` reads `mode_sampler_density` and schedules sampler events accordingly within the song's tracker timeline<br/>- evening_reflection at 0.65 produces noticeably more sampler events than working_ambience at 0.10 in 100-piece simulated runs<br/>- never schedules more sampler events than total phrases in the piece<br/>- tests verify density-to-count math, clamp behavior, and per-mode separation |
